Sara Errani and Roberta Vinci completed a career Grand Slam on Saturday, battering Timea Babos and Kristina Mladenovic to win the ladies’ doubles.

The Wimbledon crown was the only major title to have alluded the Italians but they rattled through the final in less than 56 minutes, breaking serve in the first game and easing to a 6-1, 6-3 win.

It was the second seeds’ fifth Grand Slam win as a pairing and the easiest final and they breezed through without one unforced error. They had never previously gone past the quarter-finals at the All England Club.

