Schmiedlova fought back from being a set down to beat Elena Gabriela Ruse of Romania 4-6, 6-3, 6-4, while  Ostapenko crushed 12th seed Marketa Vondrousova 6-1, 6-2.

Britain’s Jordanne Whiley will play in the ladies’ doubles wheelchair final today alongside Yui Kamiji, of Japan. 

They are top seeds and will face Jiske Griffioen and Aniek van Koot, of the Netherlands.

